<dl id="n36193e"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36193e">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36193e"> 193(e)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> scissors / pincushions</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Besides these notable pockets, they likewise wore <mark>scissors and pincushions</mark> suspended from their garments by red ribands, or among the more opulent and showy classes, by brass, and even silver chains. <small> Washington Irving, <a name="WINY" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WINY"><cite title="source">A History of New York, by Diedrich Knickerbocker</cite></a> (ed. unknown) 103</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
